{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The keyword-frequency analyzer assigns the correct sentiment when the review contains only words from the configured positive and negative word lists.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is deterministic scoring logic inside one analyzer (token counting + thresholds). No real I/O or model behavior is required; mocks would not hide the core failure.","test_description":"Call the analyzer function with in-memory positive/negative lexicons and thresholds, using reviews composed only of listed keywords (positive-only, negative-only, neutral-count cases). Assert exact sentiment label output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The explanation analyzer produces reasoning that references specific phrases from the original review, not generic boilerplate.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on generation quality from a context-interpreting analyzer. A mocked generator can trivially return phrase-grounded text and miss real model failures (generic boilerplate, weak grounding).","test_description":"Run the real explanation analyzer/model on representative reviews and assert the explanation includes concrete spans/near-quotes from the input (or explicit phrase references) rather than only generic sentiment language.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When a review contains mixed signals (both positive and negative keywords), the sentiment score reflects the configured tie-breaking rule.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic rule resolution in the keyword analyzer. Real infra is not needed to expose tie-break bugs; in-process logic tests hit the true failure boundary."